==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yaup
<hw>Yaup</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Yap</er>, and
<er>Yelp</er>.]</ety> <def>To cry out like a child; to yelp.</def>
<mark>[Scot. & Colloq. U. S.]</mark> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>yawp</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yaup</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Yaup
<hw>Yaup</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>yawp</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A cry of distress, rage, or the like, as the cry of
a sickly bird, or of a child in pain.</def> <mark>[Scot. & Colloq. U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The blue titmouse.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yauper</ent>⟦br⟧
